      <div class="row-fluid section2">
        <div class="span5 offset1 copy copy-right">
          <p>
           <b>Secure Project Payment</b> is a service oriented to project owners and developers using Bitcoin.
          </p>
          <p>  
            But why using Bitcoin with a lot of payment platforms available on the Internet? 
            Here are some benefits:
          </p>  
          <p><b>Quick and Cheap Transactions</b></p>
          <p> 
           When making a Bitcoin transfer the fees are extremely low compared to conventional methods of moving money. Accepting credit cards will generally cost 3-5% of the transfer amount, which again is much more expensive than a Bitcoin transaction(normally 0.0005 BTC per transfer). International wire transfers can take from a few days to more than a week, whereas Bitcoin transactions are generally confirmed with an hour.
          </p> 
        </div>
        <div class="span5 asset">
          <img class="img-polaroid" src="images/bitcoin.png">
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="row-fluid section1">
        <div class="span5 offset1 asset">
          <img class="img-polaroid" src="images/bitcoins.png">
        </div>
        <div class="span5 copy">
          <p><b>Irreversible Transactions</b></p>
          <p>People must be aware, when accepting credit card payments, or even bank payments, the sender has the ability to reverse or “chargeback” the payment.  There is nothing worse than sending project deliverables or code to a customer, only to receive a message that the payment has been reversed, you have been cheated and there is nothing you can do about it.</p>
<p>Bitcoin is the only payment method that is 100% irreversible and cannot be charged back, so you should be very careful when sending Bitcoins.</p>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="row-fluid section1">
        <div class="span5 offset1 copy copy-right">
          <p><b>No Paperwork</b></p>
          <p>Anyone, from any country, can accept Bitcoins within minutes.  There is no ID card, passport or proof of address that all conventional banks required to open an account.  If you are a 10 years old genius or a 30 years old senior developer you can receive a payment from your job if it is well done. All you need to do to start sending and receiving Bitcoins is to download a Bitcoin Wallet program and generate a Bitcoin Address. You can also have one or 1000 different addresses if you want.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="span5 asset">
          <img class="img-polaroid" src="images/bank-papers.png">
        </div>
      </div>


      <div class="row-fluid section1">
        <div class="span5 offset1 asset">
          <img class="img-polaroid" src="images/bitcoinusd.png">
        </div>
        <div class="span5 copy">
          <p><b>Appreciating Value</b></p>
          <p> 
            As you can see from the  <a target="_blank" href="http://www.bitcoinexchangerate.org/">Bitcoin exchange rate</a>, during the last 6 months the currency has stabilized and has been steadily increasing in value on a daily basis. During the first few years of it’s inception, the value of Bitcoins were initially highly volatile. 
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>


<div class="row-fluid section1">
        <div class="span5 offset1 copy copy-right">
          <p><b>Secure Project Payment</b></p>
          <p>The great Bitcoin advantages and too much freedom to use them, can be good or bad for businesses. The only thing we want to do, is to put a little bit of order in the chaos: we want software developers to earn money after successfully finish their projects, and we want project owners and enterprises to pay and enjoy the results. No tricks, no cheating. Everybody wins with Secure Project Payment.    
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="span5 asset">
          <img class="img-polaroid" src="images/collage1.png">
